## Extension Patterns

### When to Extend vs Create Custom

#### ✅ **Extend Spring UI Components When:**
- You need to add specific functionality to an existing component
- You want to create a specialized version of a component
- You need to combine multiple Spring UI components

```tsx
// ✅ Good: Extending Button for specific use case
import { Button, buttonVariants } from "@/components/spring-ui/button"
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

interface ActionButtonProps extends React.ComponentProps<typeof Button> {
  loading?: boolean
}

export function ActionButton({ loading, children, ...props }: ActionButtonProps) {
  return (
    <Button 
      {...props} 
      disabled={loading}
      className={cn(loading && "opacity-50", props.className)}
    >
      {loading ? "Loading..." : children}
    </Button>
  )
}
```

#### ❌ **Avoid Creating Custom When:**
- A Spring UI component already exists for the use case
- You're building something that could be composed from existing components
- You're duplicating functionality that already exists

```tsx
// ❌ Bad: Custom button when Button component exists
export function CustomButton({ children, onClick }) {
  return (
    <button 
      onClick={onClick}
      className="bg-blue-500 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded"
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  )
}

// ✅ Good: Use existing Button component
<Button variant="primary" onClick={onClick}>
  {children}
</Button>
```

## Composition Patterns

### Building Complex Layouts with Spring UI

#### Navigation Sections
```tsx
// ✅ Use Row components for navigation
<div className="space-y-1">
  <Row 
    label="Dashboard" 
    icon={<HomeIcon size={16} />} 
    selected={currentSection === 'dashboard'}
    onClick={() => setCurrentSection('dashboard')}
  />
  <Row 
    label="Settings" 
    icon={<SettingsIcon size={16} />} 
    selected={currentSection === 'settings'}
    onClick={() => setCurrentSection('settings')}
  />
</div>
```

#### Settings Forms
```tsx
// ✅ Use Row + form components for settings
<div className="space-y-4">
  <Row 
    label="Email Notifications" 
    description="Receive updates about your account"
    suffixButtons={[<Switch key="email" checked={emailEnabled} onChange={setEmailEnabled} />]}
  />
  <Row 
    label="Push Notifications" 
    description="Get notified on your device"
    suffixButtons={[<Switch key="push" checked={pushEnabled} onChange={setPushEnabled} />]}
  />
</div>
```

#### Data Tables
```tsx
// ✅ Use Table for data display
<Table>
  <TableHeader>
    <TableRow>
      <TableHead>Name</TableHead>
      <TableHead>Status</TableHead>
      <TableHead>Actions</TableHead>
    </TableRow>
  </TableHeader>
  <TableBody>
    {items.map(item => (
      <TableRow key={item.id}>
        <TableCell>{item.name}</TableCell>
        <TableCell>
          <Badge variant={item.status === 'active' ? 'green' : 'orange'}>
            {item.status}
          </Badge>
        </TableCell>
        <TableCell>
          <DropdownMenu>
            <DropdownMenuTrigger asChild>
              <IconButton variant="ghost" size="comfortable">
                <MoreIcon size={16} />
              </IconButton>
            </DropdownMenuTrigger>
            <DropdownMenuContent>
              <DropdownMenuItem>Edit</DropdownMenuItem>
              <DropdownMenuItem variant="destructive">Delete</DropdownMenuItem>
            </DropdownMenuContent>
          </DropdownMenu>
        </TableCell>
      </TableRow>
    ))}
  </TableBody>
</Table>
```

