## Common Anti-Patterns to Avoid

### ❌ **Don't Create Custom Layout Components**
```tsx
// ❌ Bad: Custom navigation item
export function NavItem({ label, icon, selected }) {
  return (
    <div className={`flex items-center p-3 ${selected ? 'bg-blue-100' : ''}`}>
      {icon}
      <span>{label}</span>
    </div>
  )
}

// ✅ Good: Use Row component
<Row 
  label={label} 
  icon={icon} 
  selected={selected}
/>
```

### ❌ **Don't Duplicate Form Logic**
```tsx
// ❌ Bad: Custom input with validation
export function CustomInput({ value, onChange, error }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <input 
        value={value} 
        onChange={onChange}
        className={`border ${error ? 'border-red-500' : 'border-gray-300'}`}
      />
      {error && <span className="text-red-500">{error}</span>}
    </div>
  )
}

// ✅ Good: Use Input component
<Input 
  value={value} 
  onChange={onChange}
  className={cn(error && "border-[var(--input-border-error)]")}
/>
```

## Summary Checklist

Before creating any custom component, ask:

1. **Is there a Spring UI component for this?** → Use it
2. **Can I compose this from existing Spring UI components?** → Compose them
3. **Do I need to extend an existing component?** → Extend it
4. **Is this truly unique functionality?** → Only then create custom

**Remember: Spring UI components are designed to be flexible and extensible. Always start with them and extend when needed.**
